<paragraph id="41AD7354852A6EAC3613F4F812BB73AA" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="35C38C5AF1672120EF4DD933DDF5C4FE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Holotype</emphasis>
, male, &quot;2017.IX.16, 
<normalizedToken id="7A436052ED24164298A40D4650967FF8" originalValue="台湾台东县金峰乡太麻里山">台湾台东县金峰乡太麻里山</normalizedToken>
, 1300 m, 
<normalizedToken id="3ACDB27F550C78D9C1A5A586D0BA796A" originalValue="周文一”">周文-&quot;</normalizedToken>
[Mount Taimalishan, Taitung County, Taiwan, 1300 m, 16.IX.2017, Wen-I Chou leg.], &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="11C1F9D96092011EDAE6C693086E1079" authorityName="Qiu &amp; Kundrata" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Pseudocsikia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pseudocsikia chanjuan" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chanjuan">
<emphasis id="DA6B52601540CE3F77F02258924FEA79" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Pseudocsikia chanjuan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. 
<normalizedToken id="34C366467A92BC32C6DDCC60D03002E7" originalValue="婵娟伪斯叩甲">婵娟伪斯叩甲</normalizedToken>
HOLOTYPE des. Qiu et Kundrata 2022&quot; (MYNU).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7471978D7FA51A19F9D4627761B2FCF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1BC0EDCD3474688DDEA7E9D4715C3738" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="09280894D4D056EE08B557EE3A8A0EC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Pronotum and elytra almost unicolored brown, but with paler apices of elytra and lateral margins of pronotum (in dry specimen condition), legs yellow (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A100A4F85E9515416505AFCD198E2BC4" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Pseudocsikia spp. A Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype, dorsal view B Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male holotype, dorsal view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691080" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">1B</figureCitation>
). Antennomere II shorter than the length of antennomere III. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A2B2AD1999501EEC90D04B7DE2519C26" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Characters of Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A pronorum, dorsal view B pro- and mesothorax, ventral view C anterior protrusion of pronotum, dorsal view D anterior protrusion of hypomeron, ventral view E antenna F posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view G metacoxal plate, ventral view H prosternal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, E, F); 0.2 mm (C, D, G, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691083" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">4A</figureCitation>
) with dense punctures (intervals usually subequal to 2-4 puncture diameters). Anterior angle of pronotum with the protrusion outward at outer angle. Posterior angle straight. Metaventrite densely punctate, intervals between punctures on average subequal to 2-3 puncture diameters. Metacoxal plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E760DB35694A67E25E337E37DAE1701F" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Characters of Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A pronorum, dorsal view B pro- and mesothorax, ventral view C anterior protrusion of pronotum, dorsal view D anterior protrusion of hypomeron, ventral view E antenna F posterior angle of pronotum, dorsal view G metacoxal plate, ventral view H prosternal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, B, E, F); 0.2 mm (C, D, G, H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691083" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">4G</figureCitation>
) short internally, surface densely covered with punctures. Tergite IX (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F96F6261B014AADF413DEF012C87F96F" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Characters of Pseudocsikia spp. A-F Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype G-L Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A, G abdominal sternite IX, dorsal view B, H abdominal tergites IX-X, dorsal view C, I abdominal sternite VIII and tergite VIII, ventral view D, J aedeagus, ventral view E, K aedeagus, lateral view F, L aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691084" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5H</figureCitation>
) suboval, with two robust lobes. Median lobe with small lateral pointed process near midlength, apical portion rounded and enlarged. Paramere with rounded apex and small process subapically. Phallobase subtrapezoidal, with slightly pointed basal angles (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0627BEAAFF569E9EC01EF6A752BA9189" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Characters of Pseudocsikia spp. A-F Pseudocsikia choui sp. nov., male holotype G-L Pseudocsikia chanjuan sp. nov., male, holotype A, G abdominal sternite IX, dorsal view B, H abdominal tergites IX-X, dorsal view C, I abdominal sternite VIII and tergite VIII, ventral view D, J aedeagus, ventral view E, K aedeagus, lateral view F, L aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691084" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D7DB928371F1D660C29C140BD29F6CF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="comparisons">
<paragraph id="1C6783BAB6BC983D46311A397104AC94" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Comparison.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38E85E62B76601FE8D5513B82FFC8FC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="F4EE74A8251A140E23B72FDC37E1933B" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. formosana" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis id="50FB60634D436B8659E6F6F49883642E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CDF94CFA8E85C5012DBE7012CD172782" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. choui" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choui">
<emphasis id="603F1024BA1E5926AF24EE39B2AE8D9B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. choui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the denser punctures of pronotum and larger body size (6.3 mm versus 4.0-5.9 mm). This new species can be further distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="93D401ACEB5C18354AC6B48F2EE72595" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. choui" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="choui">
<emphasis id="4C9B4D8DC7915FA3524977C87AF50CFC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. choui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. by the more outwardly protruded anterior angles of pronotum, and the larger and straight posterior angle of pronotum. The shape of aedeagus also differs from these. The median lobe of 
<taxonomicName id="A2DA86E8E888101E95BAAE3F44865424" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. chanjuan" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chanjuan">
<emphasis id="4210C6D2FE38BD61A28DDED6FAAB5425" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. chanjuan</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. has a slightly enlarged and rounded apex and two small acute processes laterally near midlength, its paramere is rounded at apex but with small process subapically, and the phallobase is less rounded basally than those of the other two species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="36A181009DF8FD26CFB2327165A4A56D" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1103.84015.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/691083" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
